{"title":"Phantom Mirror (spell)","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Phantom_Mirror_(spell)","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.30](/0.30 \"0.30\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n*This page is about the monster-only spell. For the evocable item, see [phantom mirror](/Phantom_mirror \"Phantom mirror\").*\n\n|   |                                                                                                                                    |\n| - | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | Creates a phantom copy of a creature. The copy will be somewhat fragile, but otherwise almost indistinguishable from the original. |\n\n**Phantom Mirror** is a monster-only spell which summons a copy of any monster in the caster's line of sight. This duplicate will have 35% of the original's [HP](/HP \"HP\"), but will otherwise be indistinguishable from the original. All decoys will disappear when the source creature or the caster is slain. The spell has a 50% chance to swap the position of the original with its phantom in order to prevent you from knowing which is real.\n\nWhen low on HP, a [rakshasa](/Rakshasa \"Rakshasa\") can create two copies of itself using this spell. These emergency clones will have 50% of the original's HP.\n\nThe following enemies cast Phantom Mirror:\n\n- R [![Rakshasa.png](/images/9/99/Rakshasa.png)](/File:Rakshasa.png) **[Rakshasa](/Rakshasa \"Rakshasa\")**\n\n## History\n\n- Prior to [0.24](/0.24 \"0.24\"), clones of other monsters would have 286% HP, and clones of a rakshasa would have 200% HP. This was a bug.\n- In [0.16](/0.16 \"0.16\"), [an item](/Phantom_mirror \"Phantom mirror\") with the same name as this spell was added.\n- Phantom Mirror was introduced in [0.14](/0.14 \"0.14\"), replacing [Rakshasa Summon](/Rakshasa_Summon \"Rakshasa Summon\").\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE ht