" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-head-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t\t<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n\t\twindow.google_analytics_uacct = \"UA-3380984-8\";\n</script>\n<div class=\"adsense\">\n\t\t<script type=\"text/javascript\"><!--\n\t\tgoogle_ad_client = \"ca-pub-7088061744296615\";\n\t\t/* CrawlWiki skyscraper */\n\t\tgoogle_ad_slot = \"8196155564\";\n\t\tgoogle_ad_width = 160;\n\t\tgoogle_ad_height = 600;\n-->\n</script>\n<script type=\"text/javascript\"\nsrc=\"http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js\">\n</script>\n</div>\n\n\t\t\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n</div>\n\t\t\t<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Phantom Mirror (spell)</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From CrawlWiki</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\" class=\"mw-jump\">\n\t\t\t\t\tJump to:\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#mw-head\">navigation</a>, \t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#p-search\">search</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div style=\"border: 1px solid #f90; background-color: #fc6; border-left: 15px solid #f90; margin-bottom: 20px; width: 100%; padding: 4px 10px; line-height: 1.1em; width: auto;\"><i><b>Version <a href=\"/0.30\" title=\"0.30\">0.30</a></b>: This article <b>may not be</b> up to date for the <a href=\"/0.32\" title=\"0.32\">latest stable release</a> of Crawl.</i></div>\n<p><i>This page is about the monster-only spell. For the evocable item, see <a href=\"/Phantom_mirror\" title=\"Phantom mirror\">phantom mirror</a>.</i>\n</p>\n<table style=\"background:#f5faff; border:1px solid #cedff2; width:auto; margin: 0px 5%; margin-bottom:1.25em; font-style:italic; text-align:left; color:#000; padding:1.5em 1em;\">\n\n<tr>\n<td>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 100%;\"> Creates a phantom copy of a creature. The copy will be somewhat fragile, but otherwise almost indistinguishable from the original.\n</td></tr></table>\n<p><b>Phantom Mirror</b> is a monster-only spell which summons a copy of any monster in the caster's line of sight. This duplicate will have 35% of the original's <a href=\"/HP\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"HP\">HP</a>, but will otherwise be indistinguishable from the original. All decoys will disappear when the source creature or the caster is slain. The spell has a 50% chance to swap the position of the original with its phantom in order to prevent you from knowing which is real.\n</p><p>When low on HP, a <a href=\"/Rakshasa\" title=\"Rakshasa\">rakshasa</a> can create two copies of itself using this spell. These emergency clones will have 50% of the original's HP.\n</p><p>The following enemies cast Phantom Mirror:\n</p>\n<ul><li> <span class=\"nhsym clr-yellow\">R</span> <a href=\"/File:Rakshasa.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Rakshasa.png\" src=\"/images/9/99/Rakshasa.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/Rakshasa\" title=\"Rakshasa\">Rakshasa</a></b></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span></h2>\n<ul><li>Prior to <a href=\"/0.24\" title=\"0.24\">0.24</a>, clones of other monsters would have 286% HP, and clones of a rakshasa would have 200% HP. This was a bug.</li>\n<li>In <a href=\"/0.16\" title=\"0.16\">0.16</a>, <a href=\"/Phantom_mirror\" title=\"Phantom mirror\">an item</a> with the same name as this spell was added.</li>\n<li>Phantom Mirror was introduced in <a href=\"/0.14\" title=\"0.14\">0.14</a>, replacing <a href=\"/Rakshasa_Summon\" title=\"Rakshasa Summon\">Rakshasa Summon</a>.</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240915230657\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\n[SMW] In‐text annotation parser time: 0.001 seconds\nCPU time usage: 0.060 se